Could this lemma and/or `starAlgHom` below be moved to the file with the rest of the `SpectrumRestricts` material, or would it screw up the imports?
Yes, it screws up imports because `SpectrumRestricts` is in `Algebra.Algebra.Spectrum`, and has no topology as a dependency.

```suggestion
`ContinuousFunctionalCalculus ℂ IsStarNormal` and produce both of the instances
`ContinuousFunctionalCalculus ℝ IsSelfAdjoint` and `ContinuousFunctionalCalculus ℝ≥0 (0 ≤ ·)`
```
I can't parse the "for characterized" bit in that docstring.
